oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Thomas Park
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a postcard featuring Thomas Park and a view of the old depot in Huntingdon. The foreground is filled with trees and flowers in bloom. Thomas Park was established in 1906 by a women's group called the Civic Improvement Club.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Parks; Trees; Flowers
